      "role": "user",
      "content": "I see. It feels like the \"innovation\" argument is basically just a way to sidestep the actual safety concerns. If we wait until after something happens to regulate, isn't it basically too late? Do you think it's actually possible to prioritize innovation while still being responsible about these existential threats, or are they just inherently at odds?",
