      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Regulatory bodies can attempt to find a middle ground, balancing innovation with safety concerns through frameworks such as responsible innovation or innovation-by-design. This approach aims to encourage developers to consider risks and values during the development process, rather than merely waiting for problems to arise. By embedding safety considerations early on, policymakers can facilitate responsible innovation that mitigates existential risks, rather than compelling developers to react to unforeseen consequences.",
